Resposta

Primerament carregarem el paquet nycflights13 i els altres paquets necessaris:

library(tidyverse)
  1. Per trobar la proporciÃ³ indicada, filtrarem els vols amb destinaciÃ³ DEST, i mirarem quina proporciÃ³ de vols provenen de lâaeroport ORIG:

flights %>%
  filter(dest %in% DEST) %>%
  summarise(
    p = mean(origin == ORIG)
  )
# > # A tibble: 1 x 1
# >       p
# >   <dbl>
# > 1 0.362
  1. Depenen de si se us demana la mitjana o la mediana, caldrÃ  canviar la definiciÃ³ de la funciÃ³ f_estad. En aquest cas hem de filtrar els vols demanats, vols que surten de ORIG i que tenen destinaciÃ³ el primer element del vector DEST.

flights %>%
  filter(origin == ORIG, dest == DEST[1]) %>%
  summarise(
    value = f_estad(dep_delay, na.rm=TRUE)
  )
# > # A tibble: 1 x 1
# >   value
# >   <dbl>
# > 1    -2
  1. En aquesta cas, per la natura de la variable, Ã©s fÃ cil veure que el retard tÃ© un fort biaix a la dreta. Podem veure-ho veient que la mitjana Ã©s bastant superior a la mediana.

  filter(origin == ORIG, dest == DEST[1]) %>%
  summarise(
    mean_ = mean(dep_delay, na.rm=TRUE),
    median_ = median(dep_delay, na.rm=TRUE)
  )
# > # A tibble: 1 x 2
# >   mean_ median_
# >   <dbl>   <dbl>
# > 1  12.5      -2
  1. Per calcular la correlaciÃ³, filtrarem els vols demanats i calcularem la correlaciÃ³. En aquest cas, Ã©s necessari eliminar el valors perduts. Per fer-ho, cal indicar-ho amb el parÃ metre use de la funciÃ³ cor().
flights %>%
  filter(origin == ORIG, dest == DEST[1]) %>%
  summarise(
    value = cor(dep_delay, arr_delay, use = "complete.obs")
  )
# > # A tibble: 1 x 1
# >   value
# >   <dbl>
# > 1 0.952

Resposta

Primerament carregarem el conjunt Pokemon:

pokemon = read_csv("quest-2-pokemon.csv")
  1. Filtrem els tipus de Pokemon demanats i comptem el nombre de files de la taula obtinguda.
TYPE1_ = "Bug"
TYPE2_ = "Grass"
pokemon %>%
  filter(TYPE1 == TYPE1_, TYPE2 == TYPE2_) %>%
  nrow()
# > [1] 6
  1. Primerament filtrarem per la condiciÃ³ TYPE == TYPE_. DesprÃ©s, per cada valor possible de la variable GENERATION, calcularem el coeficient de variaciÃ³ per la variable DEF (caldrÃ  modificar-ho per ATK en cas que es demani atac). Ordenarem per detectar el que tÃ© la major variaciÃ³.
TYPE_ = "Poison"
pokemon %>%
  filter(TYPE1 == TYPE_) %>%
  group_by(GENERATION) %>%
  summarise(.groups = 'drop',
            n = n(),
            cv = sd(DEF, na.rm=TRUE) / mean(DEF, na.rm=TRUE)    # Cal possar DEF o ATK
  ) %>%
  arrange(desc(cv))
# > # A tibble: 8 x 3
# >   GENERATION     n     cv
# >        <dbl> <int>  <dbl>
# > 1          7     8  0.472
# > 2          4     6  0.377
# > 3          1    14  0.348
# > 4          6     2  0.283
# > 5          3     3  0.240
# > 6          5     2  0.196
# > 7          8     3  0.140
# > 8          2     1 NA
  1. Comparant els diferents resultats, podem veure que sâha utilitzat el tipus Fighting:
with(filter(pokemon, TYPE1 == 'Fire'), boxplot(DEF, horizontal = TRUE))
with(filter(pokemon, TYPE1 == 'Fighting'), boxplot(DEF, horizontal = TRUE))

Resposta

Primerament descarreguem i carreguem les dades demanades:

commit = "46848f81eee15ba0d64c47e3f10eb8fbaf40bb27"
fname = "owid-covid-data.csv"
url_covid = sprintf("https://raw.githubusercontent.com/owid/covid-19-data/%s/public/data/%s",
                    commit, fname)
covid = read_csv(url_covid, 
                 col_types = cols(
                   .default = col_double(),
                   iso_code = col_character(),
                   continent = col_character(),
                   location = col_character(),
                   date = col_date(format = ""),
                   tests_units = col_character()))

data = covid %>%
  mutate(year = year(date),
         month = month(date)) %>%
  filter(year == 2020)
nrow(data)
# > [1] 50022
  1. Primer filtrem les observacions de LOCATION i comptem el nombre de casos i finalment ordenem:
LOCATION = "Greece"
data %>%
  filter(location == LOCATION) %>%
  group_by(month) %>%
  summarise(
    total = sum(new_tests, na.rm=TRUE) # new_cases, new_tests, new_deaths
  ) %>%
  arrange(desc(total))
# > `summarise()` ungrouping output (override with `.groups` argument)
# > # A tibble: 10 x 2
# >    month  total
# >    <dbl>  <dbl>
# >  1     8 347062
# >  2     9 198679
# >  3     7 195937
# >  4    10 122121
# >  5     5 105348
# >  6     6  82158
# >  7     4  53426
# >  8     3   8718
# >  9     1      0
# > 10     2      0
  1. Veient els grÃ fics veiem que el grÃ fic es va fer utilitzant Portugal.
with(filter(data, location == 'Austria'), plot(new_tests, new_cases))
with(filter(data, location == 'France'), plot(new_tests, new_cases))
with(filter(data, location == 'Portugal'), plot(new_tests, new_cases))
with(filter(data, location == 'Belgium'), plot(new_tests, new_cases))
with(filter(data, location == 'Greece'), plot(new_tests, new_cases))
